1
00:01:48,030 --> 00:01:49,620
It can't be.

2
00:01:52,870 --> 00:01:55,440
No... No...

3
00:01:56,460 --> 00:01:59,410
Pedro-san sacrificed himself...

4
00:02:02,290 --> 00:02:05,940
If only we were... if only we were...!

5
00:02:09,060 --> 00:02:11,830
If only we were stronger...

6
00:02:36,190 --> 00:02:38,880
Our enemies are the ones who should be crying.

7
00:02:39,940 --> 00:02:42,350
We cannot allow ourselves to be upset.

8
00:02:45,120 --> 00:02:46,690
Hey, Jinbe-san !

9
00:02:47,290 --> 00:02:51,360
How could you say something so cruel?!

10
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:54,980
Just because you spent the least amount of time with Pedro doesn't mean that–

11
00:02:54,980 --> 00:02:58,490
I'm just saying that we
shouldn't let our guards down!

12
00:03:00,130 --> 00:03:03,040
We had our backs against the wall
on that coastline...

13
00:03:04,390 --> 00:03:10,580
Pedro knew that we were in a dangerous situation and
was prepared to sacrifice himself whenever necessary.

14
00:03:12,340 --> 00:03:13,510
This is...

15
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:16,470
Pedro's victory!

16
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:25,850
How great of a loss has the enemy suffered
because of your presence here?

17
00:03:26,700 --> 00:03:31,320
This is an unprecedented
series of events for them!

18
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:36,780
Your strength really drove Big Mom
into a corner!

19
00:03:36,780 --> 00:03:41,790
Don't you hear Pedro's voice in your ears?!

20
00:03:44,350 --> 00:03:46,220
"Keep going!"

21
00:03:57,400 --> 00:04:00,030
Luffy understood the stakes instantly...

22
00:04:00,700 --> 00:04:04,520
and decided to take the enemy on
all by himself.

23
00:04:05,780 --> 00:04:11,530
Katakuri has a bounty of over one billion!
It's an all or nothing situation.

24
00:04:11,530 --> 00:04:14,490
But it's not over yet!

25
00:04:14,490 --> 00:04:18,370
We are still in Totto Land!

26
00:04:18,380 --> 00:04:25,750
Sooner or later, the pirate queen of this country,
Big Mom, will be on our tail!

27
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:32,130
And her fleet could close in on us
from all directions at any time!

28
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:37,130
So until we escape from Big Mom's territory...

29
00:04:37,730 --> 00:04:42,850
we must not let down our guard!
Don't you hear Pedro saying that?!

30
00:04:51,180 --> 00:04:53,090
I'm very sorry.

31
00:04:54,020 --> 00:04:56,930
I was way out of line.

32
00:04:59,390 --> 00:05:01,400
Nami, give us directions!

33
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:02,450
Okay!

34
00:05:02,450 --> 00:05:06,280
Sanji-kun and the others will be sailing to us from Cacao Island,

35
00:05:06,280 --> 00:05:08,320
so we need to make sure we don't miss them.

36
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:11,740
There's a strong wind coming!
It's a tailwind!

37
00:05:11,740 --> 00:05:13,450
So, steer to starboard!

38
00:05:13,450 --> 00:05:15,660
Hard a-starboard!

39
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:18,780
We'll catch the wind on the starboard side
and head straight west!

40
00:05:18,780 --> 00:05:20,300
We'll take a direct route!

41
00:05:20,300 --> 00:05:21,610
Roger!

42
00:05:21,610 --> 00:05:24,080
I'll go refill the cola we used!

43
00:05:27,080 --> 00:05:28,660
I'll watch for enemies!

44
00:05:31,310 --> 00:05:32,380
Okay!

45
00:05:32,380 --> 00:05:34,080
I'm in position!

46
00:05:34,080 --> 00:05:34,800
Uh-huh!

47
00:05:35,310 --> 00:05:38,080
I'll help you monitor the sea currents!

48
00:05:47,940 --> 00:05:50,370
They're coming from six o'clock!

49
00:05:50,370 --> 00:05:52,710
Those are the ships from earlier!

50
00:05:53,680 --> 00:05:54,840
There's a person?!

51
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:57,380
I-It can't be!

52
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:04,930
Cake!

53
00:06:04,930 --> 00:06:09,060
It can't be... that can't...
that can't be possible!

54
00:06:09,060 --> 00:06:12,560
Big Mom is walking on the water!

55
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:15,230
No way! That's ridiculous!

56
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:20,960
It's not water... It's...

57
00:06:22,540 --> 00:06:23,760
candy?!

58
00:06:25,410 --> 00:06:29,540
She's walking on a large blob
of moving candy!

59
00:06:30,630 --> 00:06:32,500
Using candy?!

60
00:06:32,500 --> 00:06:34,130
Hey, does that mean...?

61
00:06:35,050 --> 00:06:39,130
The only person capable of producing that...

62
00:06:39,130 --> 00:06:42,930
It must be... him !

63
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:46,640
Lick...

64
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:49,440
Candy Sea Slug!

65
00:06:49,440 --> 00:06:51,770
Where did Zeus go?

66
00:06:51,770 --> 00:06:55,650
It's his job to help Mama cross the sea!

67
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:57,320
It can't be...

68
00:06:57,340 --> 00:07:03,200
But I suppose that's fine...
because I have a score to settle with them!

69
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:06,910
Pedro sacrificed his own life!

70
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:18,110
Well, I'm able to replace
my right arm with candy, but...

71
00:07:18,110 --> 00:07:22,210
my right arm melts every time

72
00:07:22,210 --> 00:07:26,930
I try to enjoy a cup of my afternoon.

73
00:07:27,680 --> 00:07:33,590
I'll remember...
that jaguar mink's face!

74
00:07:33,590 --> 00:07:38,170
Isn't that right, Napoleon?
There's nothing more humiliating!

75
00:07:38,170 --> 00:07:42,150
It is a grievous crime in this land.

76
00:07:42,150 --> 00:07:43,830
The Straw Hats have no future here.

77
00:07:45,910 --> 00:07:48,140
How should I torment...

78
00:07:48,870 --> 00:07:52,100
his companions to sate my rage?!

79
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:02,990
Huh? Why, why, why?

80
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,630
Everyone's gone!

81
00:08:05,630 --> 00:08:10,620
I really wanna eat some flames!
I'm losing my strength...

82
00:08:10,620 --> 00:08:14,270
I wanna eat thunderclouds, too...

83
00:08:19,620 --> 00:08:24,540
Oh... So Lola-chan, who we met at Thriller Bark,
was a master at making chocolate?!

84
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:28,940
That's right. Lola was
the minister of chocolate on Cacao Island,

85
00:08:28,940 --> 00:08:33,480
but after she left,
the position was never filled!

86
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,360
Oh, how come?

87
00:08:35,360 --> 00:08:41,490
Because the presumed candidate here
keeps rejecting the position.

88
00:08:41,490 --> 00:08:42,660
Isn't that right, Pudding?

89
00:08:43,210 --> 00:08:45,780
B-Because, to me...

90
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:50,710
the only minister of chocolate
for Chocolat Town should be Sister Lola!

91
00:08:50,710 --> 00:08:54,020
And I've always hoped that she would return someday...

92
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:55,670
I know how you feel, but...

93
00:08:57,540 --> 00:08:58,720
Oh?

94
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:00,960
Oh? Oh? Oh?

95
00:09:01,270 --> 00:09:03,260
Could I be mistaken?

96
00:09:03,260 --> 00:09:04,530
No...

97
00:09:04,940 --> 00:09:08,220
I-I think that's my daughter!

98
00:09:08,220 --> 00:09:12,300
Hey! Hey!

99
00:09:15,060 --> 00:09:17,630
Hey!

100
00:09:19,380 --> 00:09:21,440
She's gone now...

101
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,610
Chiffon...

102
00:09:23,610 --> 00:09:27,660
Hey! Come out from under there, Pudding!

103
00:09:29,090 --> 00:09:31,260
N-No way!

104
00:09:31,260 --> 00:09:34,800
I'm wearing a wedding dress right now!

105
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:37,620
If I sit on the carpet with that man,

106
00:09:37,620 --> 00:09:43,600
people will think that we
just got married to each other!

107
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:46,510
What people?

108
00:09:46,510 --> 00:09:51,550
You never know who's watching!
And I'll be annoyed if they think it!

109
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:56,000
It.. It'll... It'll really annoy me, okay?!

110
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,980
Sorry about the trouble.
Just don't fall, okay?

111
00:09:59,580 --> 00:10:02,390
Sh-Shut up!

112
00:10:02,390 --> 00:10:07,700
Oh! What a sweet man!
He's worried about me!

113
00:10:07,790 --> 00:10:13,540
Who do you think you are?!
Whether I fall or not isn't your business!

114
00:10:13,540 --> 00:10:15,540
There's Cacao Island!

115
00:10:15,540 --> 00:10:18,880
All right! Let's start making the cake
as soon as we arrive!

116
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:23,690
Hey! Did you hear what I said, Sanji...

117
00:10:24,270 --> 00:10:25,670
-san ?!

118
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:30,160
What an idiot!

119
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:32,210
I can't believe he broke the mirror himself!

120
00:10:32,210 --> 00:10:35,960
Are you trying to sacrifice yourself
to let your friends escape?!

121
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:39,300
I'm gonna kick your ass!

122
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:43,040
Don't be ridiculous!

123
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:45,210
Who do you think you're talking to?!

124
00:10:45,210 --> 00:10:49,420
Commander Katakuri has a bounty
of one billion, fifty-seven million belly!

125
00:10:49,420 --> 00:10:52,680
He's the strongest
of the Three Sweet Commanders!

126
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:58,520
Hawk Gatling!

127
00:11:15,850 --> 00:11:17,830
I'm following your lead on this...

128
00:11:17,830 --> 00:11:20,340
Am I doing it wrong?

129
00:11:24,990 --> 00:11:28,240
But... it's more efficient this way!

130
00:11:36,020 --> 00:11:37,750
That's Commander Katakuri for you!

131
00:11:40,810 --> 00:11:42,930
Commander Katakuri, that's so brutal!

132
00:12:03,610 --> 00:12:05,820
I suppose you understand now.

133
00:12:10,290 --> 00:12:13,750
As I already told you...
in terms of ability...

134
00:12:13,750 --> 00:12:17,290
there's nothing you can do that I cannot.

135
00:12:17,290 --> 00:12:21,800
I have you beat in both speed and strength.

136
00:12:29,630 --> 00:12:32,680
Rubber won't lose to mochi !

137
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:44,220
I'm not gonna lose!

138
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:47,020
Gum-Gum...

139
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:50,080
Hawk Stamp!

140
00:12:52,870 --> 00:12:54,020
Is that it?

141
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:55,230
No way!

142
00:12:56,090 --> 00:12:57,380
He disappeared again!

143
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:12,540
I knew Commander Katakuri
was in a different league!

144
00:13:21,360 --> 00:13:23,220
So you're trying strength next?

145
00:13:27,620 --> 00:13:29,180
Give up already.

146
00:13:43,380 --> 00:13:46,090
What a huge punch!

147
00:13:47,260 --> 00:13:48,970
Gum-Gum...

148
00:13:49,510 --> 00:13:51,050
Elephant...

149
00:13:52,640 --> 00:13:55,430
Gun!

150
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:04,190
Commander Katakuri's is even bigger!

151
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:37,700
Is that how you do...

152
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:39,800
your Elephant Gun?

153
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:52,570
She's so beautiful in her wedding dress!

154
00:14:52,570 --> 00:14:56,070
I feel bad for her.
Her wedding was ruined.

155
00:14:56,070 --> 00:15:00,550
But even with that sad look,
she's still so beautiful!

156
00:15:00,550 --> 00:15:03,620
Oh! It's the minister of puffs!

157
00:15:03,620 --> 00:15:05,250
M-Madam Chiffon!

158
00:15:12,460 --> 00:15:18,430
Everyone, don't worry!
Sister Chiffon is not the primary culprit of the revolt!

159
00:15:18,430 --> 00:15:23,110
The one at fault is her husband: Gang Bege!

160
00:15:24,260 --> 00:15:25,930
I'm sorry, Sister.

161
00:15:25,930 --> 00:15:32,100
I told them that I'd threaten you
and force you to help me make the cake.

162
00:15:32,100 --> 00:15:36,520
That's okay, Pudding.
That's the position I'm in now.

163
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:44,090
Well, Madam Pudding,
I can't believe what happened today...

164
00:15:44,090 --> 00:15:47,100
Who could've expected such a happy wedding

165
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:51,640
to be ruined by Straw Hat Luffy's
trespassing and Bege's betrayal?!

166
00:15:51,640 --> 00:15:56,180
That Sanji man ruined it, too!

167
00:15:56,180 --> 00:15:58,250
What's done is done.

168
00:15:58,250 --> 00:16:01,530
Madam Pudding, I'm sure
you're having a hard time!

169
00:16:01,530 --> 00:16:04,570
Mama must be angry.

170
00:16:04,570 --> 00:16:07,820
Yes, she's mad and hungry.

171
00:16:08,560 --> 00:16:12,900
In addition, she's on a ravenous rampage
and may very well destroy this country.

172
00:16:12,900 --> 00:16:15,700
Oh, how horrible...

173
00:16:15,700 --> 00:16:17,330
Is everything ready?

174
00:16:17,330 --> 00:16:25,550
Yes! About an hour ago, the 31 most renowned chefs
from Whole Cake Island arrived here.

175
00:16:40,170 --> 00:16:43,590
We've been expecting you, Madam Pudding!

176
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:48,820
We're the 31 head chefs
of Whole Cake Island!

177
00:16:48,820 --> 00:16:52,270
We're the WCI 31!

178
00:16:52,270 --> 00:16:59,080
Sister Chiffon and I will make
the wedding cake that can stop Mama.

179
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:00,780
Please help us.

180
00:17:00,780 --> 00:17:05,240
Yes, ma'am!
We've already made preparations!

181
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:11,040
Madam Pudding was the bride,
so she was affected the most by what happened...

182
00:17:11,040 --> 00:17:15,920
You can count on me!
I'm not gonna let Mama destroy our country!

183
00:17:15,920 --> 00:17:17,670
Madam Pudding!

184
00:17:17,670 --> 00:17:23,710
I can't believe she's overcoming the pain
and overseeing the cake-making herself!

185
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:26,300
She's literally a goddess of salvation!

186
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:27,600
Good luck!

187
00:17:28,300 --> 00:17:31,590
Go ahead and go inside with Rabiyan.

188
00:17:31,590 --> 00:17:32,510
Okay.

189
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:35,620
Please, everyone! Listen to me!

190
00:17:35,620 --> 00:17:38,390
I need you to do me a favor!

191
00:17:38,390 --> 00:17:43,960
We're going to risk our lives and bake the cake
that will determine the fate of our country!

192
00:17:43,960 --> 00:17:46,240
We really need to concentrate!

193
00:17:47,670 --> 00:17:53,410
So, please don't look inside the factory
under any circumstance while we're at it!

194
00:17:53,410 --> 00:17:54,240
Yes, ma'am!

195
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:59,720
And no matter who it is,
don't let anyone look inside!

196
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:00,460
Yes, ma'am!

197
00:18:00,460 --> 00:18:03,620
We understand, Madam Pudding!

198
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:06,680
Thank you, everyone!

199
00:18:07,920 --> 00:18:10,740
Good luck, Madam Pudding!

200
00:18:11,510 --> 00:18:14,070
This way, they won't see Sanji-san...

201
00:18:14,070 --> 00:18:18,050
And now, I've got to deal with the ones
who will be helping us.

202
00:18:19,470 --> 00:18:23,620
Head Chefs! Come inside one at a time!

203
00:18:28,230 --> 00:18:32,330
Head chef of the First Kitchen,
Buche, reporting for duty.

204
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:41,040
Stay still.

205
00:18:43,810 --> 00:18:45,800
I'm gonna modify your memories...

206
00:18:45,800 --> 00:18:46,840
Edit!

207
00:18:47,660 --> 00:18:49,400
Hey, let me down.

208
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,130
Okay!

209
00:18:50,130 --> 00:18:52,460
Here you go!

210
00:18:52,460 --> 00:18:54,050
That must've been a tough ride.

211
00:18:54,060 --> 00:18:55,930
We don't have much time,

212
00:18:55,930 --> 00:18:59,310
so I drew a blueprint of the wedding cake on the way here.

213
00:18:59,310 --> 00:19:01,270
What?! You memorized it?

214
00:19:01,270 --> 00:19:02,650
Pretty much.

215
00:19:02,650 --> 00:19:08,200
No way! It's easy to remember the shape, but how
could you know the ingredients without tasting it?!

216
00:19:14,360 --> 00:19:15,580
By smelling it.

217
00:19:15,580 --> 00:19:17,040
Seriously?!

218
00:19:17,950 --> 00:19:22,340
Now, hurry up! Every minute counts!

219
00:19:23,490 --> 00:19:27,970
Pudding-chan's chef outfit is so cute!

220
00:19:27,970 --> 00:19:29,230
What?!

221
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:33,520
Madam Pudding, are you all right?!

222
00:19:33,520 --> 00:19:35,680
Let's do it, Sir Husband!

223
00:19:35,680 --> 00:19:36,800
Huh? Me?

224
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,310
Come here!

225
00:19:38,320 --> 00:19:42,080
I took out their memories
of the incident earlier...

226
00:19:42,080 --> 00:19:45,910
In other words, they think
the wedding finished without a hitch, and...

227
00:19:45,910 --> 00:19:50,280
that w... we are... m... married!

228
00:19:51,360 --> 00:19:52,730
But...

229
00:19:53,780 --> 00:19:57,720
they think the wedding cake was ruined
by unexpected weather

230
00:19:57,720 --> 00:20:01,790
and that Mama was enraged,
so the cake has to be remade quickly.

231
00:20:01,790 --> 00:20:04,500
That is what they believe now.

232
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:05,540
I see.

233
00:20:05,540 --> 00:20:12,710
Their memories of making the cake
are still fresh, so they'll be useful to us!

234
00:20:14,340 --> 00:20:18,930
Who drew this blueprint
and recipe for the wedding cake?!

235
00:20:18,930 --> 00:20:20,180
Me!

236
00:20:20,180 --> 00:20:22,600
Sir Husband, you drew this?!

237
00:20:22,600 --> 00:20:25,770
Yeah. Let me know if there are any mistakes.

238
00:20:25,770 --> 00:20:27,370
It's perfect!

239
00:20:27,370 --> 00:20:30,000
You even identified the hidden flavors

240
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:33,410
that took Head Chef Streusen
a week to come up with!

241
00:20:33,410 --> 00:20:37,740
I heard rumors you were skilled, but wow, you're amazing!

242
00:20:37,740 --> 00:20:42,290
And by an odd coincidence,
as husband and wife...

243
00:20:42,290 --> 00:20:43,460
Husband and wife?!

244
00:20:43,460 --> 00:20:47,520
..this cake will be your first project,
strangely enough.

245
00:20:48,410 --> 00:20:50,790
Yeah, you're right. I'm a little embarrassed.

246
00:20:50,790 --> 00:20:52,880
Husband and wife...

247
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:56,470
Are you okay, Madam Wife?!

248
00:20:54,930 --> 00:20:56,470
W... Wife...

249
00:20:56,470 --> 00:20:57,910
Madam Wife!

250
00:20:57,340 --> 00:20:57,900
W...

251
00:20:57,900 --> 00:20:59,740
Madam Wife! Madam Wife!

252
00:20:59,060 --> 00:20:59,740
W-W...

253
00:20:59,740 --> 00:21:01,600
Stay with us, Mada–

254
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:03,310
Stop! She'll die!

255
00:21:03,310 --> 00:21:04,440
What?!

256
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:08,060
He called us husband and wife! Oh my!

257
00:21:08,060 --> 00:21:09,440
Hey!

258
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:12,580
What? He suddenly said "Hey" to me!

259
00:21:12,580 --> 00:21:16,540
Maybe it's not so bad
to have an assertive husband...

260
00:21:16,540 --> 00:21:20,190
No, but it's important to start things right.

261
00:21:20,190 --> 00:21:25,500
I-If you act like my master,
I'll kill you, Sanji...

262
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:27,290
I need you to gather these as fast as you can.

263
00:21:27,290 --> 00:21:32,100
Non-homogenized milk, sugar beets,
bananas, black sesame,

264
00:21:32,100 --> 00:21:35,340
roasted soy flour, yogurt.
A lot of it.

265
00:21:35,340 --> 00:21:36,540
Yes, sir!

266
00:21:37,590 --> 00:21:39,430
...-san !

267
00:21:40,970 --> 00:21:45,640
Everyone! It's a race against time
until the cake is complete!

268
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:50,370
Chiffon-chan, you bake
the giant chiffon cake.

269
00:21:50,370 --> 00:21:54,480
Pudding-chan, you handle
all the chocolate tempering.

270
00:21:55,530 --> 00:21:58,420
You have two hours and 40 minutes!

271
00:21:58,440 --> 00:22:01,830
It certainly is a fight against time.

272
00:22:01,830 --> 00:22:06,540
When we get there,
I'll add my secret ingredient!

273
00:22:06,540 --> 00:22:10,310
It can lead anyone to the peak of happiness...

274
00:22:10,310 --> 00:22:13,380
I'll make you taste true sweetness!

275
00:22:13,380 --> 00:22:16,920
T-True sweetness?!

276
00:22:16,920 --> 00:22:22,490
In three hours, we'll load the incomplete cake
on a ship and leave Cacao Island.

277
00:22:22,490 --> 00:22:27,200
And as we let it cool down,
we'll decorate it on the ship.

278
00:22:27,200 --> 00:22:31,580
Before we return to the Sunny where Luffy
and the others are being chased by Big Mom,

279
00:22:31,580 --> 00:22:34,860
we'll finish making the greatest cake ever!

280
00:22:34,860 --> 00:22:37,280
I see. That sounds efficient.

281
00:22:37,280 --> 00:22:39,400
But at that fast of a pace?

282
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:41,450
No matter how you look at it,
that's impossible!

283
00:22:41,450 --> 00:22:44,840
We gotta do it!
Do you want Mama to destroy the country?!

284
00:22:44,840 --> 00:22:48,040
I'm sorry! We'll follow you!

285
00:22:49,700 --> 00:22:51,110
All right!

286
00:22:51,460 --> 00:22:53,020
Let's start baking!

287
00:22:54,380 --> 00:22:56,870
For those who saved Lola!

288
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:59,970
For Sanji-san !

289
00:22:59,970 --> 00:23:06,230
I'll make my special extremely-fluffy
chiffon cake!

290
00:23:06,230 --> 00:23:09,440
I must help Sanji-san and the others get away!

291
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:12,430
With my very sweet chocolate!

292
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:16,650
Keep hanging on, guys!

293
00:23:17,650 --> 00:23:19,170
I'll show them!

294
00:23:20,020 --> 00:23:22,270
My offensive cooking!

295
00:23:26,700 --> 00:23:29,100
Katakuri, it's me.

296
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:31,930
You managed to survive, Brother Peros.

297
00:23:31,930 --> 00:23:33,650
Yes, barely.

298
00:23:33,650 --> 00:23:37,420
That bastard Pedro...

299
00:23:37,420 --> 00:23:40,250
died so pathetically!

300
00:23:40,250 --> 00:23:43,630
Straw Hat! You were there, weren't you?

301
00:23:45,910 --> 00:23:52,140
I suppose he sacrificed his life to try and kill me,

302
00:23:52,140 --> 00:23:55,180
but I'm very much alive,
as you can probably tell.

303
00:23:55,900 --> 00:23:59,730
So he died for no reason!
Right?!

304
00:23:59,730 --> 00:24:04,450
And now you're going to die in vain too,
just like Pedro.

305
00:24:04,450 --> 00:24:08,150
Why don't you let him kill you already?
Lick.

306
00:24:08,150 --> 00:24:10,670
What happened to Straw Hat's friends?

307
00:24:10,670 --> 00:24:12,840
Believe it or not,

308
00:24:12,840 --> 00:24:15,520
they launched their ship into the air
and escaped our encirclement.

309
00:24:15,520 --> 00:24:18,340
I'm chasing them with Mama now...

310
00:24:18,340 --> 00:24:21,300
We're walking on the water.

311
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:26,220
They're tenaciously trying to flee,
but we'll catch up to them soon.

312
00:24:26,220 --> 00:24:29,890
Amande and the others' fleet
will be here soon, too.

313
00:24:29,890 --> 00:24:30,800
I see.

314
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:34,100
Brûlée.

315
00:24:35,990 --> 00:24:38,460
Ah, Big Brother...

316
00:24:38,460 --> 00:24:43,390
How long do you plan on sleeping?
Our soldiers can't go anywhere if you keep doing that.

317
00:24:43,390 --> 00:24:44,370
Okay.

318
00:24:44,370 --> 00:24:47,800
I thought he might have been able to protect his crew with all of that vigor he's got,

319
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:49,400
but this is the current state of their captain.

320
00:24:49,400 --> 00:24:53,260
Take those soldiers
and go set fire or something to Straw Hat's ship.

321
00:24:53,260 --> 00:24:54,280
Okay!

322
00:24:54,280 --> 00:24:56,040
Big Sister Brûlée!

323
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:59,430
We found a mirror that goes to Straw Hat's ship!

324
00:24:59,430 --> 00:25:01,500
There must be one or two more!

325
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:06,170
All right! Let's shoot flaming arrows
at Straw Hat's ship!

326
00:25:06,170 --> 00:25:11,970
I hope they're taken out by Mama
while in a frenzy from the fire.

327
00:25:12,620 --> 00:25:13,760
Yikes!

328
00:25:18,530 --> 00:25:21,230
Give me that mirror!

329
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:23,520
Leave them alone!

330
00:25:24,960 --> 00:25:28,680
I thought you wanted to have a one-on-one duel with me, Straw Hat.

331
00:25:30,090 --> 00:25:32,300
That's what you get!

332
00:25:36,010 --> 00:25:41,280
Now, burn down Straw Hat's ship!

333
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:43,400
Roger!

334
00:25:46,390 --> 00:25:48,820
Are you ready, Joscar?

335
00:25:48,820 --> 00:25:51,060
I am, Mascar.

336
00:25:57,510 --> 00:26:00,750
Now, shoot them!

337
00:26:04,350 --> 00:26:06,410
Stop!!

338
00:26:16,910 --> 00:26:18,480
Stop!

339
00:26:18,480 --> 00:26:20,810
No, you stop.

340
00:26:20,810 --> 00:26:25,860
Leave my precious
younger brother and sisters alone!

341
00:26:33,680 --> 00:26:35,620
A mirror!

342
00:26:39,370 --> 00:26:41,040
Hey, Nami!

343
00:26:44,240 --> 00:26:46,490
Jinbe, can you hear me?!

344
00:26:46,910 --> 00:26:48,920
Somebody, respond!

345
00:27:03,940 --> 00:27:06,640
Hey! Can you hear me?! Somebody!

346
00:27:06,640 --> 00:27:07,850
What? Luffy?!

347
00:27:07,850 --> 00:27:09,080
Nami!

348
00:27:10,620 --> 00:27:12,600
Luffy, it's me! Are you okay?!

349
00:27:12,840 --> 00:27:15,640
There are still some mirrors on the ship, right?!

350
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:16,300
What?!

351
00:27:16,300 --> 00:27:18,850
Maybe in the mens' bedroom or the bathroom?!

352
00:27:23,130 --> 00:27:26,070
It's burning up!

353
00:27:26,070 --> 00:27:27,910
We're gonna shoot, Joscar.

354
00:27:27,910 --> 00:27:30,030
Yes, we are, Mascar.

355
00:27:31,510 --> 00:27:34,120
It's burning! It's burning!

356
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:38,790
Luffy?! What'd you say about mirrors?!

357
00:27:38,790 --> 00:27:41,130
Break them all! To pieces!

358
00:27:41,130 --> 00:27:45,880
Are you out of your mind?!
How will you come back if we do that?!

359
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:48,880
I don't know, but I'll be fine!

360
00:27:49,620 --> 00:27:51,800
I'll figure something out!

361
00:27:52,740 --> 00:27:54,120
Sniff, sniff...

362
00:27:55,830 --> 00:27:57,490
I smell something!

363
00:27:57,490 --> 00:27:59,880
I don't have a nose, though!

364
00:28:02,560 --> 00:28:03,690
What?

365
00:28:04,920 --> 00:28:07,070
The bathroom is on fire!

366
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:09,090
What's wrong?!

367
00:28:10,030 --> 00:28:12,180
How is this happening?!

368
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:15,700
What?!

369
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:21,600
Flaming arrows from inside the mirror!
Cannon shots from behind!

370
00:28:21,600 --> 00:28:24,350
One thing after the other!
My eyes are spinning!

371
00:28:24,350 --> 00:28:27,420
Oh, I don't have eyes that can spin!

372
00:28:27,420 --> 00:28:29,980
In any case, let's put it out, Brook!

373
00:28:32,200 --> 00:28:35,100
Now, you guys, keep shooting!

374
00:28:35,100 --> 00:28:37,350
We're gonna keep shooting, Joscar.

375
00:28:37,350 --> 00:28:40,270
Yes, we are, Mascar.

376
00:28:40,270 --> 00:28:42,610
Stop it, you bastards!

377
00:28:48,130 --> 00:28:49,900
Luffy!

378
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:52,320
Luffy! Are you okay?!

379
00:28:54,590 --> 00:28:58,430
Those of you who'll march onto the ship,
follow me!

380
00:29:00,040 --> 00:29:01,480
Oh, no!

381
00:29:09,150 --> 00:29:12,800
Nami! Hurry up and break the mirrors!
All of them!

382
00:29:12,800 --> 00:29:13,930
But...

383
00:29:13,930 --> 00:29:18,760
Our enemies are sending an army your way!
I can't stop them by myself!

384
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:22,520
Let me focus just on this guy!

385
00:29:27,790 --> 00:29:28,840
Huh?

386
00:29:32,090 --> 00:29:34,030
Nami! We have a problem!

387
00:29:35,050 --> 00:29:37,160
We can't get away!

388
00:29:40,190 --> 00:29:42,130
A high wave!

389
00:29:42,130 --> 00:29:43,000
What?!

390
00:29:46,340 --> 00:29:48,460
Are you there...?

391
00:29:59,350 --> 00:30:02,450
I'm sorry, Luffy...

392
00:30:03,230 --> 00:30:07,100
I won't let you get away!

393
00:30:07,120 --> 00:30:10,070
Nami! What's wrong?!

394
00:30:10,070 --> 00:30:12,640
We...

395
00:30:12,640 --> 00:30:15,530
might be done for...

